---
import ProjectLayout from '../../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro'
---

<ProjectLayout
  lang="en"
  title="AI Collaboration in Practice: Building a Custom Portfolio Solo in Two Weeks"
  headline="A record of how I apply AI in real-world workflows. Using this portfolio site as a case study — from zero to launch in two weeks — AI both expanded my capability boundaries and refined my existing craft, while I built up a methodology for collaboration."
  skills={['AI Orchestration', 'Prompt Design', 'Claude Code', 'Context Engineering']}
  roles={['Product Designer', 'AI Orchestration Architect']}
>

  <!-- 1. Starting Point -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">1. Starting Point: From "Constrained Layouts" to "Independent Development"</h2>
    <p class="text-black leading-relaxed mb-4">
      My previous portfolio was constrained by an existing platform's framework, making it hard to fully express my design style. At the same time, I lacked hands-on experience with frontend development and deployment.
    </p>
    <div class="border-l-2 border-black pl-4 py-1">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/50 mb-1">Core Goal</p>
      <p class="text-black leading-relaxed">
        Use AI as a collaborator to independently build a fully customized portfolio in two weeks.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. Process -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-2">2. Process: Two Weeks, Five Stages</h2>
    <p class="text-black/60 leading-relaxed mb-8 text-sm">
      From research to launch, AI played a different role at each stage. Here's the full collaboration trail.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Step 01 -->
      <div class="border border-black/10 p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6 md:gap-10">
          <div class="md:w-[180px] shrink-0">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/50 mb-1">Step 01</p>
            <p class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-black/40 mb-3">Day 1–2</p>
            <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-black leading-snug">Research & Planning</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <ul class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside mb-4">
              <li>Built a custom portfolio-analysis skill, then dissected 5 designer portfolios to extract layout structure, typographic rhythm, and interaction patterns</li>
              <li>Had Claude Code draft portfolio-plan.md, defining page architecture, tech stack, and information hierarchy</li>
              <li>Established the site-wide visual tone (black & white core + serif headlines)</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <span class="text-xs bg-black text-white px-3 py-1">Claude Code</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 02 -->
      <div class="border border-black/10 p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6 md:gap-10">
          <div class="md:w-[180px] shrink-0">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/50 mb-1">Step 02</p>
            <p class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-black/40 mb-3">Day 3–5</p>
            <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-black leading-snug">Design & Spec</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <ul class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside mb-4">
              <li>Used Figma Make to rapidly produce static mockups & motion drafts</li>
              <li>Built a modular component inventory (Hero / ProjectCard / Footer…)</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <span class="text-xs bg-black text-white px-3 py-1">Figma AI</span>
              <span class="text-xs bg-black text-white px-3 py-1">Claude Chat</span>
              <span class="text-xs bg-black text-white px-3 py-1">Spec-driven Prompting</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 03 -->
      <div class="border border-black/10 p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6 md:gap-10">
          <div class="md:w-[180px] shrink-0">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/50 mb-1">Step 03</p>
            <p class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-black/40 mb-3">Day 6–10</p>
            <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-black leading-snug">Development & Integration</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <ul class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside mb-4">
              <li>Asked AI for recommendations, then locked in Astro project setup and Tailwind configuration</li>
              <li>Had AI translate the spec into Astro components one by one</li>
              <li>Built reliable Git habits with AI: Push, Commit, resolving Conflicts</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <span class="text-xs bg-black text-white px-3 py-1">Claude Code</span>
              <span class="text-xs bg-black text-white px-3 py-1">GitHub Copilot</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 04 -->
      <div class="border border-black/10 p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6 md:gap-10">
          <div class="md:w-[180px] shrink-0">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/50 mb-1">Step 04</p>
            <p class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-black/40 mb-3">Day 11–12</p>
            <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-black leading-snug">QA & Edge Cases</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <ul class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside mb-4">
              <li>Sent screenshots to AI for a second pass on layout alignment, type hierarchy, and responsive behavior</li>
              <li>Simulated edge scenarios: extra-long copy, multilingual switching</li>
              <li>Closed the loop on design quality: surfaced what did and didn't meet my expectations and fed it back to AI so the next iteration could apply the lessons</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 05 -->
      <div class="border border-black/10 p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-6 md:gap-10">
          <div class="md:w-[180px] shrink-0">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/50 mb-1">Step 05</p>
            <p class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-black/40 mb-3">Day 13–14</p>
            <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-black leading-snug">Launch & Retrospective</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <ul class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside mb-4">
              <li>Configured the Vercel deployment environment and pointed the custom domain</li>
              <li>Post-launch, asked AI to review the entire collaboration flow, and continuously extracted optimization points based on interview feedback</li>
              <li>Captured the technical lessons learned back into reusable notes</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <span class="text-xs bg-black text-white px-3 py-1">Claude Code (Vercel CLI)</span>
              <span class="text-xs bg-black text-white px-3 py-1">Skill: retro</span>
              <span class="text-xs bg-black text-white px-3 py-1">Second Brain (Notion AI)</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3. Horizontal Expansion -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-2">3. Horizontal Expansion: New Skills Unlocked by AI</h2>
    <p class="text-black/60 leading-relaxed mb-6 text-sm">
      Capabilities I couldn't have completed independently before — now within reach with AI.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-3">Engineering & Architecture</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Built the entire site solo (Astro / Tailwind)</li>
          <li>Set up an i18n multilingual structure</li>
          <li>Got comfortable with Git version control (Push / Commit / resolving Conflicts)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-3">Deployment Automation (DevOps)</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Independently handled Vercel deployment configuration</li>
          <li>Domain pointing and binding</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-3">Personal Tooling</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Built a custom job-advisor script</li>
          <li>Automated the mechanical chores of job hunting</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4. Vertical Refinement -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-2">4. Vertical Refinement: Output Quality Lifted by AI</h2>
    <p class="text-black/60 leading-relaxed mb-6 text-sm">
      Areas where I was already strong — AI helped move "good" toward "polished."
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-2">Translating Logic into Specs</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          Converting "design requirements" into "engineering specs," keeping the build aligned to the original prototype.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-2">Deep Research & Analysis</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          Rapidly analyzing competitor layouts to extract design patterns; iterating copy through dialogue with AI to land on the most precise tone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-2">Design Quality QA</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          Using screenshots to ask AI for a second-pass check on alignment, type hierarchy, and responsive fit.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-2">Edge-Case Testing</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          Simulating extreme conditions (very long copy, broken images) to harden the CSS handling early.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. Decisions & Risk Management -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">5. Decisions & Risk Management in AI Collaboration</h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="border border-black/10 p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/50 mb-2">01</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-2">Document-Driven Development</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          A grounding portfolio-plan.md plus modular components reduced AI hallucinations and saved on token spend.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-black/10 p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/50 mb-2">02</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-2">Tech Knowledge Base (Second Brain)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          Captured technical details (e.g., Astro syntax) into a personal knowledge base in real time, so I'd stop re-asking AI the same questions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-black/10 p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/50 mb-2">03</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-2">Proactive Backups</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          Built a manual backup habit to compensate for AI not flagging risk on its own.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-black/10 p-6">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/50 mb-2">04</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-black mb-2">Reverse Calibration After Each Session</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          After each collaboration, asked AI to self-review the process, or pulled in community-shared review skills — continuously tuning the rapport between AI and me.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. Retrospective -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-2">6. Retrospective: How I'd Do It Better Next Time</h2>
    <p class="text-black/60 leading-relaxed mb-8 text-sm">
      Three adjustments I'd try if I were starting over.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-0">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[100px_1fr] gap-3 md:gap-8 py-8 border-t border-black/10">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/40">01</p>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-3"><span class="highlight-underline">Lean on existing tooling sooner</span></h3>
          <p class="text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
            I'd start from open-source design.md files released by larger companies rather than exploring from scratch. A portfolio is closer to a back-office product than a marketing site — clarity of information is what matters; bespoke flourishes are bonus, not core. Starting from a "passing-grade" foundation and customizing on top is a more efficient path to the goal.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[100px_1fr] gap-3 md:gap-8 py-8 border-t border-black/10">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/40">02</p>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-3"><span class="highlight-underline">Invest in the outline, not late-stage prompt patching</span></h3>
          <p class="text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
            Early on I rushed to see results before refining details, but downstream patching is far less efficient than a clear outline up front. Deciding what's load-bearing and producing a structurally sound outline is what I want to keep sharpening.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[100px_1fr] gap-3 md:gap-8 py-8 border-t border-b border-black/10">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-black/40">03</p>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-3"><span class="highlight-underline">Draw the line between modular blocks and bespoke detail</span></h3>
          <p class="text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
            The outline should pre-classify which sections suit off-the-shelf tooling (data displays, UI components) versus which need heavy customization (mental-model diagrams, narrative pieces). A clear boundary lowers the cognitive load on both me and the AI, and makes future iterations more logical and consistent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 7. Reflections -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-[20px] font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">7. Reflections</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-2 border-black pl-5 py-1">
        <p class="text-base font-semibold text-black mb-1">Finishing is easy. Finishing well is hard.</p>
        <p class="text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          AI gets you to 60 quickly; getting past 80 takes professional skill, and going beyond that takes several times more focused craft on top of the AI's output.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-2 border-black pl-5 py-1">
        <p class="text-base font-semibold text-black mb-1">Usable, but not yet excellent</p>
        <p class="text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          The output still needs human polish to reach the ideal. Closing the gap between AI's notion of "good work" and a designer's is a long-term, ongoing problem to work on.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-2 border-black pl-5 py-1">
        <p class="text-base font-semibold text-black mb-1">Stay connected — don't build in a vacuum</p>
        <p class="text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
          AI is a journey of continuous learning. Keeping in touch with the community through social platforms and small industry meetups is how I keep absorbing new tools and approaches, instead of going in circles alone.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>
